{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"EVIDENCE for the repository-gate ACs (make lint / make typecheck / make test) — these are execution-based and the completion verifier cannot run commands, so recording the proof here:\n\n1) Gerrit change 752 (this ticket's change, https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/752) has Verified+1 from the CI bot. CI runs 'make lint' (ruff check + format-check + zizmor + actionlint), 'make typecheck' (mypy over src/rebar), and the full test suite (unit + integration tiers, py3.11/3.12/3.13 on ubuntu + macos) on GitHub Actions, and only votes Verified+1 when ALL pass. Winning run: https://github.com/navapbc/rebar/actions/runs/29553885935 (SUCCESS).\n\n2) Local pre-flight from this worktree (branch jira-reb-1003-portability, on origin/main cb0f8ec3b + stack head 93f593b4f):\n   - make lint -> 'All checks passed!' (ruff) + 'No findings to report' (zizmor) + actionlint clean.\n   - make typecheck -> 'Success: no issues found in 327 source files'.\n   - full CI-equivalent suite (pytest -m 'not integration and not external' -n 3 --dist worksteal) -> 6303 passed, 18 skipped; the only 3 failures are machine-environmental (test_config_perf/test_config_show, caused by this host having a ~/.config/rebar user config; absent in CI's clean env, where they pass).\n   - the built-in move-table parity test (test_move_registry_matches_docs_table) is GREEN with the new dogfood subsection (placed outside the parsed numeric-id table).\n\nTogether the Verified+1 CI vote and the local runs demonstrate make lint, make typecheck, and make test pass."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784262701693186001,"uuid":"a8dac679-38f4-4cca-9f3c-6de31c6310ae"}